Well.

3
00:06:20,797 --> 00:06:23,216
Apparently, we’re
getting new neighbours soon, too.

4
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:25,635
Yeah?

5
00:06:25,676 --> 00:06:27,345
Yeah.

6
00:06:31,808 --> 00:06:33,601
When’s your train going?

7
00:06:34,769 --> 00:06:36,354
As usual?

8
00:06:37,522 --> 00:06:38,648
Yes.

9
00:06:38,689 --> 00:06:39,816
At 10.

10
00:06:40,817 --> 00:06:42,360
As every monday.

11
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:00,878
.

12
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:08,469
I had a dream.

13
00:07:09,846 --> 00:07:10,972
Want to hear it?

14
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:15,268
With friends I entered an old warehouse.

15
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:23,276
White lamps illuminated 
a room of white tiles and walls 

16
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:24,444
which yet were dirty.

17
00:07:25,153 --> 00:07:26,654
There also stood a shelf

18
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:30,408
with things on it
which I did not understand.

19
00:07:31,409 --> 00:07:33,119
We attempted to have ourselves frozen

20
00:07:33,744 --> 00:07:35,788
to get unfrozen again in the future.

21
00:07:36,706 --> 00:07:38,583
Having arrived I learned…

22
00:07:43,379 --> 00:07:47,258
Having arrived I learned 
that we were not to choose

23
00:07:47,258 --> 00:07:48,468
when precisely.

24
00:07:48,676 --> 00:07:51,888
Not even getting unfrozen together

25
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:53,598
was ours to decide.

26
00:07:57,101 --> 00:07:58,936
I had it done anyways. 

27
00:08:00,563 --> 00:08:03,274
After all, it was already paid for.

28
00:08:57,578 --> 00:08:57,620
.

29
00:08:58,204 --> 00:08:59,580
And how are you?

30
00:09:00,831 --> 00:09:02,166
So-so.

31
00:09:03,292 --> 00:09:05,711
I’m almost done with preparation.

32
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:07,672
But it's not that important.

33
00:09:09,590 --> 00:09:11,300
I’m starting to get a bit nervous.

34
00:09:12,093 --> 00:09:15,179
But I’m also happy
because the day is coming closer.

35
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:17,598
And now,

36
00:09:18,140 --> 00:09:20,309
with all the others
supposedly coming to us...

37
00:09:23,187 --> 00:09:26,816
I mean I always wanted to see New Zealand.

38
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:29,110
And I’m also coming back, I guess.

39
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:41,163
Before I forget:

40
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,630
When my brother was here

41
00:09:51,549 --> 00:09:53,342
he gave me a card.

42
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:01,017
You can keep it if you want.

43
00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:08,065
Think of me when looking at it.

44
00:10:12,236 --> 00:10:16,407
Before I leave
we will definitely do something together.

45
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:18,451
I promise.

46
00:11:18,469 --> 00:11:18,511
.

47
00:11:18,594 --> 00:11:20,388
What's new?

48
00:11:20,763 --> 00:11:22,890
Some of them have bitten my mother.

49
00:11:23,474 --> 00:11:24,684
It was quite horrible.

50
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:27,103
My father and I cried.

51
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,480
It all went very fast,
I mean:

52
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,439
her transformation.

53
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:34,860
At first her wound
swelled red and mother stopped speaking.

54
00:11:35,403 --> 00:11:39,573
Her gums turned black
and she stopped washing herself.

55
00:11:40,282 --> 00:11:43,994
After a while she sat down
on the chair and stopped moving.

56
00:11:44,578 --> 00:11:48,416
The neighbours already started gossiping,
why one did not see her anymore

57
00:11:48,416 --> 00:11:51,627
and why the shutters
on our living room were always let down.

58
00:11:51,961 --> 00:11:55,005
When a neighbour’s boy
tried to press the shutters upwards 

59
00:11:55,089 --> 00:11:57,133
we had to move her into the cellar.

60
00:11:57,216 --> 00:12:00,886
At that time her body
was already covered with ulcerous bumps.
